Accessibility

Use this form to request any reasonable adjustment you might require during the application or interview process due to a disability.

Disability is a strength. People with disabilities make our company stronger by helping us make better products to achieve our mission to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. Microsoft offers a variety of accommodations or adjustments for candidates with medical needs or disabilities.

Wait until you're scheduled for an interview or technical assessment before requesting an accommodation. In the meantime, you can visit the Accessibility page to get more info about the variety of accommodations and adjustments Microsoft supports.

If you're scheduled for an interview or online technical assessment, use this form to send your request. You have a variety of ways to request accommodation or adjustments. Choose the one that will best demonstrate your skills and experience. Here are a few examples:

  • Live captions
  • Scheduling adjustments
  • Sign Language Interpreter
  • Cart Writer
  • Camera off
To ensure your accommodation will be in place on the day of your interview or online technical assessment align your request with the job ID.

Any accommodations request will only be used for one role. It doesn't stay with your candidate profile beyond the interview stage..

You, the undersigned Candidate, have been invited to interview for possible employment with Microsoft Corporation ("Microsoft") subject to the following understanding. Microsoft is interested in talking with you based upon your general knowledge, background, experience and skills and abilities, and not because of your knowledge of any confidential information or trade secrets belonging to your current or prior employer(s) or to any other person or entity. At no time will you disclose to Microsoft or use in your discussions with Microsoft any confidential or proprietary information or trade secrets of any current or prior employer or any other entity or person. You will not bring onto Microsoft property any documents or other materials in tangible form containing any confidential or proprietary information or trade secrets belonging to any other person or entity.


Further, in the course of your interviews, Microsoft may in its discretion disclose confidential information to you. In consideration of the disclosure of such confidential information by Microsoft, you hereby agree as follows:


1. Confidential Information and Materials


"Confidential Information" of Microsoft means nonpublic information that Microsoft designates as being confidential or that, under the circumstances surrounding disclosure, ought to be treated as confidential. Confidential Information includes, without limitation:

  • a) technical, financial, marketing, manufacturing, distribution or other business information or trade secrets of Microsoft, including without limitation concepts, techniques, processes, methods, systems, designs, circuits, cost data, computer programs, formulas, development or experimental work, work in progress, customers and suppliers, and business policies or practices;

  • b) information relating to unreleased Microsoft products or the marketing or promotion of such products;

  • c) information received from others that Microsoft is obligated to treat as confidential.

"Confidential Materials" of Microsoft means all tangible materials containing Confidential Information, including unreleased Microsoft products and documentation. "Confidential Information" does not include information that Candidate receives from a third party who is not subject to an obligation to maintain the confidentiality of such information, or information that is publicly available. If you have any questions concerning whether certain information is Confidential Information, you should ask your interviewer or your Microsoft recruiter.


2. Candidate's Obligations


You shall not disclose any Confidential Information or Materials to third parties for two (2) years following the date of its disclosure by Microsoft to you.

Hello {{formResponse<2004787654611603>}} {{formResponse<2004787654611604>}}! Welcome to Microsoft Recruiting references page.

{{candidateFullName}} listed you as a reference in their application to Microsoft Research and is requesting a reference letter from you.

The reference letter review is an important step in our screening process. Select yes to upload the reference letter or if you prefer not to submit a reference, please select no. Note that candidates don't have access to the letter provided, but we do notify them when a reference declines or provides the letter.
After you submit the form, we'll email your contact.
View the travel and expense policy and enter details for your interview-related expenses. Make sure your name and email are correct in your profile.
Review

Microsoft offers a variety of accommodations or adjustments for candidates with medical needs, disabilities or religious beliefs. Accommodations are very personal and individualized depending on each unique candidate and their circumstances. You do not need to disclose the nature of your disability. Requesting an accommodation is completely voluntary and is not required if you do not need support.

Your request won't be a part of your candidate profile beyond the current stage in your application or on future applications. Please open new requests as needed. Please reach out directly to your scheduler or recruiter for general scheduling preferences or questions which are outside the scope of this intake.

label: I see the value of Microsoft Career Hub and how it can help me unlock and accelerate my career at Microsoft.
I can create a Profile that accurately represents my skills, experiences, and interests.
My Career Navigator recommendations are relevant to me.
I can easily find projects relevant to my interests that can help me build new skills and experiences.
As a mentee, I can easily find and connect with mentors that match my goals and interests.

The survey will take approximately 3-5 minutes to complete. Participation in this survey is voluntary. Results are not anonymous, but identifiable responses are confidential and only accessible by a small number of employees in the HR people analytics group for analytical purposes. Your management will not have access to any identifiable responses.

This survey will provide Microsoft feedback about the recently launched Microsoft Career Hub platform. Your input will help inform decisions to improve the platform experience.
